text: Holy keyed
#DarkPeat

Had a really deep human voice that slowly transformed into the usual cooing noises as I awoke, I think "for you" was said towards his female pigeon partner to dedicate the song to her. Really felt like a Medieval fairy tale of being granted the talent to understand animal speech.

Woke up early in the morning in an in-between semi-awake state where I kept seeing some old (Church Slavonic?) script in front of my eyes and I could understand the animal speech of the wood pigeon cooing on the tree next to my window. He was saying "for you, for you, for you..."

For me it's my sense of smell, when I did a fast I would be able to smell any food cooked in my neighborhood from my apartment window, someone could be making fried fish on the other side of the block and I'd immediately sense it and run to my balcony smelling at the air/wind lol

I wonder how common religious miracles are in Amish communities or Mennonites, etc. Or how common paranormal encounters are, if the Amish see folklore creatures more often than normal rural people. And also other religious communities like Orthodox Jews, Jehovah's Witnesses, etc.

Seeing stay at home mothers' lifestyle here and it seems they are outdoors w/ their children basically the entire day. Children w/ stay at home moms probably get 20 times more sunlight than daycare children. Enough to set your lifelong health on a completely different trajectory.

Feels like back in the day being a "stay at home mother" was more home-centric (it's in the name too), nowadays they're just spending 10 hours between the farmers' market and the park playground. Benefits of less neurotic culture about having guests over or stuff like that.

Reminds me of that Maine taxi driver story of him and his girlfriend going ice skating at a frozen pond and seeing the ice start shaking and something bubbling under supposedly due to hot gases deep underground but him perceiving it as a lake monster. Geology leading to folklore.

Bodybuilders talk about how doing growth hormone makes their muscles watery and Dr. Ray Peat also mentions how HGH is related to fluid regulation and causes water retention and if you read Andre The Giant drinking stories he could drink 12 beers without having to piss afterwards.

Like one Andre anecdote was him having 30 beers at the back of a bus/car and after hours of driving never asked to stop for a bathroom break, driver even checked seat and floor to see if he pissed himself or smth but nope his body just held 30 beers. Driver told story on podcast.

They probably exchanged letters, I recall Dr. Peat said he wrote letters or emails to most of the researchers he tends to mention or cite often in the articles. He even had correspondence with Chomsky and Maslow iirc. Lots of famous ppl write you back if you send them a letter...

Dr. Linus Pauling himself has an absolutely huge archive, his work and projects are all very well documented, institutes dedicated to him, etc... Anyone interested can find info easily on the internet and dig in very deeply there. Especially if you have a solid base in chemistry.
